{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, the development history of each interaction method can be seen in Figure 3.",
    "Assuming that z is the retrieved message, x is the input, y is the output, and F is a function, either a language model or a data processing function, with x and z as independent variables, the basic architecture of RALM is defined as follows:",
    "The sequential single interaction process involves finding the Top-K relevant documents z to input x through a retriever P η (z|x), where η is a parameter of the retriever.",
    "Subsequently, the language model P θ (y i |x, z, y r) receives input x along with relevant documents z and outputs the i-th token y i.",
    "Parameter θ is used, along with relevant output tokens y r."
  ]
}